a-transfer/dataSource.description: Used for setting the source data. The elements that are part of this array will be present the left column. Except the elements whose keys are included in `targetKeys` prop., Default: \[]

a-transfer/filterOption.description: A function to determine whether an item should show in search result list, Default:

a-transfer/footer.description: customize the progress dot by setting a scoped slot, Default:

a-transfer/listStyle.description: A custom CSS style used for rendering the transfer columns., Default:

a-transfer/locale.description: i18n text including filter, empty text, item unit, etc, Default: `{ itemUnit: 'item', itemsUnit: 'items', notFoundContent: 'The list is empty', searchPlaceholder: 'Search here' }`

a-transfer/oneWay.description: Display as single direction style, Default: false

a-transfer/operations.description: A set of operations that are sorted from top to bottom., Default: \['>', '<']

a-transfer/operationStyle.description: A custom CSS style used for rendering the operations column, Default: -

a-transfer/pagination.description: Use pagination. Not work in render props, Default: false

a-transfer/render.description: The function to generate the item shown on a column. Based on an record (element of the dataSource array), this function should return a element which is generated from that record. Also, it can return a plain object with `value` and `label`, `label` is a element and `value` is for title, Default:

a-transfer/selectedKeys(v-model).description: A set of keys of selected items., Default: \[]

a-transfer/showSearch.description: If included, a search box is shown on each column., Default: false

a-transfer/showSelectAll.description: Show select all checkbox on the header, Default: true

a-transfer/targetKeys(v-model).description: A set of keys of elements that are listed on the right column., Default: \[]

a-transfer/titles.description: A set of titles that are sorted from left to right., Default: -

a-tree/autoExpandParent.description: Whether to automatically expand a parent treeNode, Default: false

a-tree/blockNode.description: Whether treeNode fill remaining horizontal space, Default: false

a-tree/checkable.description: Adds a `Checkbox` before the treeNodes, Default: false

a-tree/checkedKeys(v-model).type: string[] | number[] | {checked: string\[] | number\[], halfChecked: string\[] | number\[]}
a-tree/checkedKeys(v-model).description: (Controlled) Specifies the keys of the checked treeNodes (PS: When this specifies the key of a treeNode which is also a parent treeNode, all the children treeNodes of will be checked; and vice versa, when it specifies the key of a treeNode which is a child treeNode, its parent treeNode will also be checked. When `checkable` and `checkStrictly` is true, its object has `checked` and `halfChecked` property. Regardless of whether the child or parent treeNode is checked, they won't impact each other., Default: \[]

a-tree/checkStrictly.description: Check treeNode precisely; parent treeNode and children treeNodes are not associated, Default: false

a-tree/defaultExpandAll.description: Whether to expand all treeNodes by default, Default: false

a-tree/disabled.description: whether disabled the tree, Default: false

a-tree/draggable.description: Specifies whether this Tree is draggable (IE > 8), Default: false

a-tree/expandedKeys(v-model).description: (Controlled) Specifies the keys of the expanded treeNodes, Default: \[]

a-tree/fieldNames.description: Replace the title,key and children fields in treeNode with the corresponding fields in treeData, Default: { children:'children', title:'title', key:'key' }

a-tree/filterTreeNode.description: Defines a function to filter (highlight) treeNodes. When the function returns `true`, the corresponding treeNode will be highlighted, Default: -

a-tree/loadedKeys.description: (Controlled) Set loaded tree nodes. Need work with `loadData`, Default: \[]

a-tree/multiple.description: Allows selecting multiple treeNodes, Default: false

a-tree/selectable.description: whether can be selected, Default: true

a-tree/selectedKeys(v-model).description: (Controlled) Specifies the keys of the selected treeNodes, Default: -

a-tree/showIcon.description: Shows the icon before a TreeNode's title. There is no default style; you must set a custom style for it if set to `true`, Default: false

a-tree/showLine.description: Shows a connecting line, Default: false

a-tree/switcherIcon.type: v-slot:switcherIcon="{active, checked, expanded, loading, selected, halfChecked, title, key, children, dataRef, data, defaultIcon, switcherCls}"
a-tree/switcherIcon.description: customize collapse/expand icon of tree node, Default: -

a-tree/treeData.description: treeNode of tree, please use `treeNodes` before v1.1.4, Default: -

a-tree/virtual.description: Disable virtual scroll when set to false, Default: true

a-tree/scrollTo({ key: string | number;.description: Scroll to key item in virtual scroll, Default: undefined

a-tree-node/checkable.description: When Tree is checkable, set TreeNode display Checkbox or not, Default: -

a-tree-node/disableCheckbox.description: Disables the checkbox of the treeNode, Default: false

a-tree-node/icon.description: customize icon. When you pass component, whose render will receive full TreeNode props as component props, Default: -

a-tree-node/isLeaf.description: Determines if this is a leaf node(effective when `loadData` is specified), Default: false

a-tree-node/key.description: Used with (default)ExpandedKeys / (default)CheckedKeys / (default)SelectedKeys. P.S.: It must be unique in all of treeNodes of the tree!, Default: internal calculated position of treeNode

a-tree-node/selectable.description: Set whether the treeNode can be selected, Default: true

a-directory-tree/expandAction.description: Directory open logic, optional `false` `'click'` `'dblclick'`, Default: click

a-typography-text/content(v-model).description: When using ellipsis or editable, use content instead of children, Default: -

a-typography-text/copyable.description: Whether to be copyable, customize it via setting an object, Default: false

a-typography-text/editable.description: If editable. Can control edit state when is object, Default: false

a-typography-text/ellipsis.description: Display ellipsis when text overflows, Default: false

a-typography-title/content(v-model).description: When using ellipsis or editable, use content instead of children, Default: -

a-typography-title/copyable.description: Whether to be copyable, customize it via setting an object, Default: false

a-typography-title/editable.description: If editable. Can control edit state when is object, Default: false

a-typography-title/ellipsis.description: Display ellipsis when text overflows, can configure rows and expandable by using object, Default: false

a-typography-title/level.description: Set content importance. Match with `h1`, `h2`, `h3`, `h4`, `h5`, Default: 1

a-typography-paragraph/content(v-model).description: When using ellipsis or editable, use content instead of children, Default: -

a-typography-paragraph/copyable.description: Whether to be copyable, customize it via setting an object, Default: false

a-typography-paragraph/editable.description: If editable. Can control edit state when is object, Default: false

a-typography-paragraph/ellipsis.description: Display ellipsis when text overflows, can configure rows and expandable by using object, Default: false

a-upload/accept.description: File types that can be accepted. See [input accept Attribute](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/file#accept), Default: -

a-upload/beforeUpload.description: Hook function which will be executed before uploading. Uploading will be stopped with `false` or a rejected Promise returned., Default: -

a-upload/customRequest.description: override for the default xhr behavior allowing for additional customization and ability to implement your own XMLHttpRequest, Default: -

a-upload/data.description: Uploading params or function which can return uploading params., Default: -

a-upload/fileList.description: List of files that have been uploaded (controlled). Here is a common issue [#2423](https://github.com/ant-design/ant-design/issues/2423) when using it, Default: -

a-upload/headers.description: Set request headers, valid above IE10., Default: -

a-upload/isImageUrl.description: Customize if render <img /> in thumbnail, Default: -

a-upload/itemRender.type: v-slot:itemRender="{originNode: VNode, file: UploadFile, fileList: object[], actions: { download: function, preview: function, remove: function }"

a-upload/listType.description: Built-in stylesheets, support for three types: `text`, `picture` or `picture-card`, Default: `text`

a-upload/maxCount.description: Limit the number of uploaded files. Will replace current one when `maxCount` is `1`, Default: -

a-upload/method.description: http method of upload request, Default: `post`

a-upload/multiple.description: Whether to support selected multiple file. `IE10+` supported. You can select multiple files with CTRL holding down while multiple is set to be true, Default: false

a-upload/name.description: The name of uploading file, Default: `file`

a-upload/openFileDialogOnClick.description: Click open file dialog, Default: true

a-upload/progress.description: Custom progress bar, Default: { strokeWidth: 2, showInfo: false }

a-upload/showUploadList.type: boolean | { showPreviewIcon?: boolean, showRemoveIcon?: boolean, showDownloadIcon?: boolean }
a-upload/showUploadList.description: Whether to show default upload list, could be an object to specify `showPreviewIcon`, `showRemoveIcon` and `showDownloadIcon` individually, Default: true

a-upload/supportServerRender.description: Need to be turned on while the server side is rendering., Default: false

a-upload/withCredentials.description: ajax upload with cookie sent, Default: false

a-upload-file/status.description: Upload status. Show different style when configured, Default: -

a-upload-file/uid.description: unique id. Will auto generate when not provided, Default: -
